The paper deals with the problem of expert finding on StackOverflow, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also proposes two translation models, which involve machine learning and natural language processing techniques, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another likely category. The paper also uses word embeddings, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new approach that takes the quality of documents into account, which involves ranking and scoring techniques, making cs.DL (Digital Libraries) a possible category as well.
